  "text": "Now, as I understand it, the archetypes are the the biases of a very fundamental nature that under free will generate the experiences of each entity. Is this correct? I and Raw. The archetypical mind is part of that mind which informs all experience. Please recall the definition of the archetypical mind as the repository of those refinements to the cosmic or all mind made by this particular a logos and peculiar only to this logos. Thus it may be seen as one of the roots of mind, not the deepest, but certainly the most informative in some ways. The other route of mind to be recalled is that racial or planetary mind, which also informs the conceptualizations of each entity to some degree.",
